.TH "Vinyl" "1" "" "Version 0.1.1" "Vinyl Manual Page Documentation"
.SH NAME
io.github.libredeb.vinyl \- A fullscreen music experience
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]io.github.libredeb.vinyl\f[R]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Vinyl is a desktop music player that provides a beautiful, fullscreen
interface to your music library.
Built with Vala and SDL2, it is designed for those who appreciate a clean
aesthetic and intuitive control.
Whether you prefer using your keyboard or a gamepad, Vinyl offers a
seamless way to navigate your tunes without ever needing to reach for
a mouse.
.SH MUSIC LIBRARY
Music is read from the \f[B]XDG_MUSIC_DIR\f[R] user directory,
typically \f[I]~/Music\f[R].
.PP
Supported formats: \f[B].mp3\f[R], \f[B].flac\f[R], \f[B].ogg\f[R],
\f[B].wav\f[R].
.SH FILES
.TP
\f[I]$XDG_DATA_HOME/vinyl/library.db\f[R]
Library database. Typically \f[I]~/.local/share/vinyl/library.db\f[R].
.TP
\f[I]$XDG_CACHE_HOME/vinyl/covers\f[R]
Cover art cache directory. Typically \f[I]~/.cache/vinyl/covers\f[R].
.SH CONTROLS
.TP
\f[B]Keyboard\f[R]
Full keyboard navigation is supported for browsing and playback.
.TP
\f[B]Gamepad\f[R]
SDL2 game controller support for a couch\-friendly experience.
.SH BUGS
Report bugs at \f[I]https://github.com/libredeb/vinyl/issues\f[R].
